00:54.630 --> 00:57.714
I hope I haven't been
keeping you waiting.

00:57.716 --> 00:58.882
Robert.

00:58.884 --> 01:01.017
I don't think
we've seen each other

01:01.019 --> 01:03.136
since law school graduation.

01:04.188 --> 01:06.022
You haven't changed.

01:06.024 --> 01:07.557
So what can I do for you?

01:07.559 --> 01:09.309
Um, I'm really just
here as a courtesy.

01:09.311 --> 01:11.311
I'm working for the attorney
general's office now,

01:11.313 --> 01:14.114
and I've been assigned
your brother Danny's case.

01:14.116 --> 01:15.282
What case?

01:15.284 --> 01:16.483
Thomas Wilder.

01:16.485 --> 01:17.567
No, that case is done.

01:17.569 --> 01:18.902
The shooting was deemed
justified.

01:18.904 --> 01:20.954
New evidence
has turned up.

01:20.956 --> 01:22.923
What new evidence?

01:22.925 --> 01:25.492
The Wilder family
submitted some audio tapes.

01:25.494 --> 01:26.660
Of what?

01:26.662 --> 01:27.878
I'm sorry, but
I can't really talk

01:27.880 --> 01:29.329
about the particulars
with you.

01:29.331 --> 01:31.131
Why not?

01:31.133 --> 01:33.300
Because I'm gonna
have to question

01:33.302 --> 01:34.468
you and your daughter.

01:34.470 --> 01:36.503
You were ear-witnesses
to the killing.

01:36.505 --> 01:37.671
It was self-defense.

01:37.673 --> 01:39.973
That'll be up to
the grand jury.

01:45.764 --> 01:47.681
(sighs)

01:47.683 --> 01:49.065
I don't have to
remind you

01:49.067 --> 01:50.901
that it wouldn't be
standard procedure?

01:50.903 --> 01:52.152
No, you don't.

01:52.154 --> 01:53.603
You sure you want
to do this?

01:53.605 --> 01:55.989
That's exactly
what I want to do.

01:57.159 --> 01:58.108
They're here, sir.

01:58.110 --> 02:00.193
Okay.
I'll take care of it.

02:00.195 --> 02:01.495
FRANK:
Grace.

02:03.866 --> 02:05.031
So good to see you.

02:05.033 --> 02:06.583
Aw, you, too, Frank.

02:06.585 --> 02:08.668
(door closes)
Louis.

02:08.669 --> 02:10.453
Frank.

02:10.455 --> 02:12.122
We got a beautiful day for it.

02:12.124 --> 02:13.874
(sighs) We did.

02:13.876 --> 02:15.342
Please.

02:17.679 --> 02:19.513
So, how's the academy
treating you, Louis?

02:19.515 --> 02:21.014
Treating me like
the rookie I am.

02:21.016 --> 02:22.549
You want me to pull
some strings for you?

02:22.551 --> 02:24.501
Would you?
No.

02:24.503 --> 02:25.719
Thought so.
(chuckles)

02:27.222 --> 02:28.471
How we doing?

02:28.473 --> 02:30.724
Good. Yeah.

02:33.278 --> 02:35.612
Okay, here's how this goes.

02:35.614 --> 02:38.064
We ride over together
with my detail.

02:38.066 --> 02:41.067
I give a brief talk
remembering Martin,

02:41.069 --> 02:43.703
the cop he was,
sacrifice he made.

02:43.705 --> 02:45.288
Then we unveil

02:45.290 --> 02:47.073
the street sign,
take a few pictures,

02:47.075 --> 02:50.794
and then I'd like to take
you both to lunch, if you can.

02:51.964 --> 02:53.797
Well, thank you.

02:53.799 --> 02:56.016
I can't believe
it's been ten years.

02:56.018 --> 02:58.635
You were all of what,
Louis, 11?

02:58.637 --> 03:01.087
Yeah. Seems like both
a lifetime ago

03:01.089 --> 03:03.557
and also just yesterday.

03:03.559 --> 03:06.059
Yeah, well, your dad
would be proud

03:06.061 --> 03:08.094
that you're following
in his footsteps.

03:08.096 --> 03:10.180
And selfishly, I am glad

03:10.182 --> 03:12.015
that this particular apple
didn't fall

03:12.017 --> 03:13.683
too far from the tree.

03:15.787 --> 03:17.571
They're ready for
you out front, sir.

03:17.573 --> 03:18.772
Okay.

03:18.774 --> 03:21.107
Honey, would you give me
a moment with Frank?

03:21.109 --> 03:23.276
Yeah. Sure, Mom.

03:26.682 --> 03:30.116
(door opens, closes)

03:30.118 --> 03:33.119
I'm sure it'll be
a lovely tribute, Frank.

03:33.121 --> 03:35.021
You've always been good
at the dedications

03:35.023 --> 03:37.524
and the eulogies.

03:37.526 --> 03:41.011
Something's on your mind, Grace.

03:42.848 --> 03:47.317
Since Louis joined the academy,
I've hardly slept a wink.

03:47.319 --> 03:48.802
Well, if he needs help
with anything,

03:48.804 --> 03:50.720
you know I'm just
a phone call away.

03:50.722 --> 03:52.689
I mean, you've been there
for every birthday,

03:52.691 --> 03:54.608
championship, graduation.

03:54.610 --> 03:56.226
And I am really
looking forward

03:56.228 --> 03:59.029
to graduating him
from the academy.

04:00.098 --> 04:02.232
I do have one favor to ask.

04:03.535 --> 04:05.352
Okay.

04:06.655 --> 04:10.106
Make sure Louis does not
graduate the academy.

04:10.108 --> 04:13.827
Kick him out, fail
him, disqualify him.

04:13.829 --> 04:16.096
I don't care what you do.

04:16.098 --> 04:19.916
Anything to ensure that
he does not become a cop.

04:25.524 --> 04:27.641
Where are we gonna put
all this stuff?

04:27.643 --> 04:29.142
We're gonna need
a bigger apartment.

04:29.144 --> 04:31.394
Sophie, favorite gift today.

04:31.396 --> 04:33.763
The nail pens.
The rainbow quicksand!

04:33.765 --> 04:36.349
You know we're gonna be cleaning
that stuff up for weeks.

04:36.351 --> 04:37.901
(tires screeching)

04:37.903 --> 04:39.352
Sophie!
(both scream)

04:44.159 --> 04:45.859
HELEN:
Sophie, no!

04:45.861 --> 04:47.444
Oh... oh, my God!
(car alarm blaring)

04:47.446 --> 04:49.446
PAUL:
Sophie!

04:49.448 --> 04:50.447
God, no!

04:50.449 --> 04:52.532
"Other than your parents,

04:52.534 --> 04:55.702
who is the most influential
person in your life, and why?"

04:55.704 --> 04:59.039
Joe. Because he encouraged me
to go for what I really want

04:59.041 --> 05:00.840
instead of what other
people wanted for me.

05:00.842 --> 05:02.375
Hmm.

05:02.377 --> 05:04.044
I think he recognized
that I spent a lot of time

05:04.046 --> 05:05.295
trying to make
other people happy.

05:05.297 --> 05:06.796
Not in this partnership.

05:06.798 --> 05:09.182
DISPATCHER (over radio):
12 David, be advised we have

05:09.184 --> 05:11.134
a 53, pedestrian struck,

05:11.136 --> 05:13.553
corner of Broadway
and nine-seven street.

05:13.555 --> 05:15.355
12 David to Central,
we're en route.

05:15.357 --> 05:16.890
(siren wailing)

05:22.731 --> 05:24.531
PAUL: Sophie!
JAMIE: What happened?

05:24.533 --> 05:26.900
This car came out of nowhere,
and it hit my daughter.

05:26.902 --> 05:28.668
Eddie, call it in.
Oh, God. Oh, my God!

05:28.670 --> 05:30.286
Central, 12 David,
we have multiple injuries

05:30.288 --> 05:31.738
at this location.

05:31.740 --> 05:34.240
Come on, Sophie, come on,
baby, come on, honey.

05:34.242 --> 05:35.575
Ma'am, you've got to calm down!
Sophie!

05:35.577 --> 05:36.427
She's unconscious?

05:36.428 --> 05:37.121
We're doing
everything we can.

05:37.125 --> 05:38.161
PAUL:
Helen, stay with Zach!

05:38.163 --> 05:39.546
(sobbing):
Oh, my God!

05:41.083 --> 05:43.166
That's him.
He plowed into us.

05:43.168 --> 05:45.251
That son of a bitch was driving
like a freakin' lunatic!

05:45.253 --> 05:47.137
Hey, whoa, hey, hey! Hey!

05:47.139 --> 05:48.888
Take care of your family.

05:48.890 --> 05:51.141
You all right?
Yeah.

05:51.143 --> 05:53.226
You guys all right?
Yeah.

05:53.228 --> 05:54.594
Yeah, we're okay.

05:54.596 --> 05:56.930
Were you driving?
Yeah.

05:56.932 --> 05:58.898
Where were you coming from?
(sniffs)

05:58.900 --> 06:00.817
Fund-raiser at the Waldorf.

06:00.819 --> 06:03.153
Have you been drinking?
No.

06:03.155 --> 06:04.571
I'm asking him.

06:04.573 --> 06:06.606
Not me. I wasn't drinking.

06:06.608 --> 06:08.441
Gonna need you to take
a Breathalyzer test.

06:09.995 --> 06:11.021
No.

06:11.045 --> 06:12.464
You refusing
a Breathalyzer?

06:13.448 --> 06:14.914
You feeling okay, Russ?

06:14.916 --> 06:17.200
I'm having chest pains.
I need to see a doctor.

06:17.202 --> 06:19.119
STILLER:
Yeah.

06:19.121 --> 06:20.754
This is Congressman
Russ Anderson.

06:20.756 --> 06:22.288
Who's under arrest for DWI.

06:22.290 --> 06:25.208
He needs medical attention,
Officer Reagan.

06:26.344 --> 06:29.129
You denying him
medical attention?

06:29.131 --> 06:30.964
Central, 12 David.
We need an additional bus

06:30.966 --> 06:33.216
at this location and
a patrol supervisor.

06:33.218 --> 06:35.185
I'll ride with him
to the hospital.

06:35.187 --> 06:36.719
And I'll be back
with a warrant

06:36.721 --> 06:38.755
for his blood alcohol.

